  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion, carrot, and celery and cook until the vegetables are tender.",
    "Add the chicken to the pot and cook until browned on all sides.",
    "Add the garlic granules, black pepper, chicken broth, thyme, and salt to the pot.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Let the stew rest for 10 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld together.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or over rice for a filling meal."
